fields.description:
Bamboo lists Perforce commits in my build result's Commits tab that aren't included in my current workspace.

I have a Perforce repository organized like this:

{quote}
//my_depot/top/a
//my_depot/top/b
//my_depot/top/c
{quote}

I created a Perforce workspace like this:

{quote}
//my_depot/top/... //my_workspace/top/...
{quote}

I configured a build plan like this:

* Repositories
** Client (workspace): my_workspace
** Depot view: //my_workspace/top/...
** Let Bamboo manage your workspace: Yes
** Use client mapping for change detection: No

I ran the build plan.

Then I modified the workspace to look like this:

{quote}
//my_depot/top/a/... //my_workspace/top/a/...
//my_depot/top/b/... //my_workspace/top/b/...
{quote}

Then I ran the build plan again.

Observed behavior: Commits in //my_depot/top/c were listed in my build result Commits tab even though they are not included in the workspace.

Expected behavior: Only commits in //my_depot/top/a and //my_depot/top/b are listed.

Error message: {noformat}The current identity (IP-0A0984F0\Bamboo) does not have write access to 'C:\Windows\Microsoft.NET\Framework\v4.0.30319\Temporary ASP.NET Files'{noformat}

Customer suggestion: The identity should really have write access to paths matching 'C:\Windows\Microsoft.NET\Framework\v*\Temporary ASP.NET Files'.

Also would it be possible to include .Net v4.5 in the Windows 2008 image?

At the moment, users can run customized builds to run a certain revision of the build. This however does not build based on the previously saved configuration in case there was changed. Here is a use case
{quote}
I found this "customised manual build" in the documentation. But i don't see, if the build configuration is also stored/versioned. E.g. in my build 1050 I use java 7 to compile (and the java version is configured in the bamboo build configuration). In build 1251 I change to java 8. Some time later I want to build a custom/historical build with the configuration from build 1050 (--> java 7).
{quote}

i see this in all of my builds:
{noformat}
Unable to find executable at &('C:\Program Files\Bamboo\temp\SMA-MAS1-BTP-107-ScriptBuildTask-2100663733811810433.ps1'). Will try to run it anyway.
{noformat}

The error message is related to a very simple power shell script. The script runs without issue, but it's kind of annoying to see these show up in the error summary of successful builds.

This appears to be in nature, very similar to BAM-12124 but for powershell scripts instead of batch scripts. Hopefully the resolution is also similar.

We plan on upgrading our bamboo server to the latest version very shortly, so please let me know if this issue has already been resolved in a newer build.

h5. Workaround
Move the java tmp dir out of _Program Files_
# Edit {{Bamboo Install/bin/catalina.bat}}
# Look and comment out {{set "CATALINA_TMPDIR=%CATALINA_BASE%\temp"}}:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed}
rem set "CATALINA_TMPDIR=%CATALINA_BASE%\temp"
{noformat}
# Add a new line to set the new temp location. Example:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed}
set "CATALINA_TMPDIR=C:\bambootemp"
{noformat}
# Restart Bamboo

